In response to the request, I have written the following source code for Timsort in Lean 4:

`class Timsort:

    def sort(self, list):
        def partition(i, j):
            pivot = list[i]
            k = i
            while (j - k) > 1:
                while (list[k] <= pivot):
                    k += 1
                if k > i:
                    t = list[k]
                    list[k] = list[j]
                    list[j] = t
                j -= 1
            return k, j

        l, r = partition(i, len(list) - 1)
        pivot = list[r]
        list[r], list[l] = list[l], list[r]
        for i in range(l + 1, r):
            pivot = self.partition(i, r)
            if self.compare(list[i], pivot) < 0:
                self.swap(list, i, pivot)
        return l, r`

