Here is a program in C++ that reads a file line by line and counts the number of appearances of a specific word in the file. A function called `count_word()` counts the number of appearances of a given word in a given line.

```C++
// Counts the number of occurrences of a word in a text file.
// Returns the total number of occurrences.
int count_word(const char* word, const char* file_name) {
    // Open the file to read from.
    std::ifstream input(file_name);
    if (input) {
        // Read the file line by line.
        int counter = 0;
        while (input) {
            // Get the current line from the input stream.
            std::string line;
            input >> line;
            if (line.find(word) != std::string::npos) {
                counter++;
            }
        }
        return counter;
    } else {
        throw std::runtime_error("Could not open file.");
    }
}
